ABSTRACT
The rapid evolution of technology and the growing interconnectedness of our digital world have necessitated the creation of secure and intelligent networks that can adapt to the dynamic demands of today's information age. In this context, this abstract describes a research or development effort aimed at Enabling a secure intelligent network with cloud-assisted privacy-preserving machine learning.  In an era where data privacy and security are paramount concerns, the proposed approach seeks to combine the strengths of cloud computing and privacy-preserving machine learning to build a network infrastructure that is not only intelligent but also highly secure. Cloud assistance provides the scalability and computational resources required for complex machine learning tasks, enabling the network to make informed decisions and optimize its operations.  Crucially, privacy-preserving machine learning techniques are employed to ensure that sensitive data and user information remain protected. These techniques allow the network to learn from data without exposing the raw, confidential information, thereby safeguarding the privacy of individuals and organizations.  The research aims to bridge the gap between the ever-increasing need for intelligent, data-driven decision-making and the imperative to maintain robust data privacy and security. By integrating cloud computing and privacy-preserving machine learning, this work seeks to pave the way for the development of a secure, intelligent network environment that can meet the challenges of our data-driven world while respecting privacy and confidentiality.
